A '''Heathrow injection''' is  term used for to the phenomenon of sudden and very rapid weight gain, particularly experienced by non-British persons, upon settling in London.

This is usually blamed on the availability of convenient snacks, pre-packaged sandwiches and late-night kebab shops. All of which are new and exciting to the average antipodean.
